   <title>How I pimped my TextMate</title>
   <link href="http://www.sideburns.eu/2010/02/05/how-I-pimped-my-textmate.html"/>
   <updated>Liquid error: undefined method `xmlschema' for "05/02/2010":String</updated>
   <id>http://www.sideburns.eu/2010/02/05/how-I-pimped-my-textmate</id>
   <content type="html"><p>TextMate is not very sexy when you first open it.</p>

<p><img alt='Vanilla TextMate' src='/images/TMvanilla.png' /></p>

<p>But there is some addons that I found to make it funkier.</p>

<p><img alt='Pimped TextMate' src='/images/TMpimped.png' /></p>

<p>The ProjectPlus plugin gives you SCM status badges (Git, SVN, Mercurial, Bazaar &amp; Svk), it swaps the project drawer to a panel, it can display Finder colour labels</p>

<p>New icon:</p>

<p><img alt='TextMate Icon' src='/images/TMicon.jpg' /></p>

<p>New &#8220;wallpaper&#8221;:</p>

<p><img alt='TextMate Wallpaper' src='/images/TMblank.png' /></p>

<p>ProjectPlus + Git MiniMap Icon Monokai zsh theme</p></content>
